<hr/><center><b><big><big>Building and Testing a Distribution</big></big></b></center>
<br/>
<b><big><a name="Creating Distribution Files">Creating Distribution Files</a></big></b>

<ol type="1"><li>
Change into the <code><font color="blue">CppADpackage</font></code> directory.
</li><li>

Execute the bash shell script <code><font color="blue">./Build</font></code>
</li></ol>

This will create the distribution files
<code><font color="blue">
<span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;CppADpackage/CppAD.dos.tar.gz<br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;CppADpackage/CppAD.unix.tar.gz<br/>
</span>
</font></code>
<br/>
<b><big><a name="Testing Distribution">Testing Distribution</a></big></b>

<ol type="1"><li>
Execute the command 
<code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;tar&#xA0;-xvzf&#xA0;CppAD.</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>sys</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>.tar.gz<br/>
</span></font></code>where <i>sys</i> is <code><font color="blue">dos</font></code> or <code><font color="blue">unix</font></code>
depending on your system type.
</li><li>

Execute the command
<code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;cd&#xA0;cppad-</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>yy</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>-</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>mm</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>-</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>dd</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
</span></font></code>where <code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>%yy%-%mm%-%dd%</span></font></code> is the current date.
</li><li>

Execute the command
<code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;configure&#xA0;ADOLC_DIR=</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>AdolcDir</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>&#xA0;FADBAD_DIR=</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>FadbadDir</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
</span></font></code>where the paths 
<code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>AdolcDir</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>/include/adolc/adouble.h<br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>FadbadDir</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>/FADBAD++/badiff.h<br/>
</span></font></code>are a valid way to reference the <code><font color="blue">adouble.h</font></code> file in the 
<a href="http://www.math.tu-dresden.de/~adol-c/" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>ADOLC</span></a>

distribution and the <code><font color="blue">badiff.h</font></code> in the 
<a href="http://www.imm.dtu.dk/fadbad.html/" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>FADBAD++</span></a>

distribution.
</li><li>

Execute the command
<code><font color="blue">
<span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;make<br/>
</span>
</font></code>
If no compiler errors occur, the distribution passed this test.
</li><li>

Execute the command
<code><font color="blue">
<span style='white-space: nowrap'><br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;cd&#xA0;GetStarted<br/>
&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;./GetStarted<br/>
</span>
</font></code>
If the result is
<code><font color="blue">
<br/>
<span style='white-space: nowrap'>Poly&#xA0;&#xA0;computed&#xA0;derivative&#xA0;=&#xA0;142<br/>
CppAD&#xA0;computed&#xA0;derivative&#xA0;=&#xA0;142<br/>
</span></font></code>then the distribution passed this test.
</li></ol>



